headline: The Stock Market Is Riding Its Best Day Since May as Big Tech Shines
summary: A buying frenzy in Big Tech on Monday sent the Nasdaq Composite surging toward its best day since May.  The tech-heavy index was up 2.7%, which would be its largest daily gain since May 12, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  The Dow, up nearly 300 points, or 0.6%, had stronger showings earlier this month.

headline: What the S&P 500 is hiding about the economy
summary: On its face, 2025 has been a good year for the stock market. The S&P 500 was dragged out of its tariff-induced springtime slump by a small subset of AI-forward power players whose spectacular gains defied an otherwise softening economy. Even now, despite a rocky November, the benchmark index is up more than 12 percent since the start of the year.
